  rewrite_source（纯源码 -O3）: 1.114x  [In kernel_lu, for the main triple-nested loops: (1) In loop `j < i`, before the inner `k < j` loop, declare a local double `double sum = A[i][j];`, then inside the k-loop replace `A[i][j] -= A[i][k] * A[k][j];` with `sum -= A[i][k] * A[k][j];`, and after the k-loop write back `A[i][j] = sum;`. (2) In loop `j >= i`, before the inner `k < i` loop, similarly declare `double sum = A[i][j];`, replace the accumulation, and write back after the loop. This reduces memory traffic for A[i][j] from O(inner iteration count) writes to O(1) write per (i,j) pair, while keeping all arithmetic identical.]
